---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ScrollReveal from "../components/ScrollReveal.tsx";
import { SITE } from "../config/site.mjs";
---

<Layout
	title={`About | ${SITE.title}`}
	description="My background, my approach and why I started Silverbeet Technology"
	canonicalURL={`${SITE.url}/about`}
>
	<Header />
	<main id="main-content" role="main">
		<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
			<ScrollReveal client:idle>
				<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">About</h1>
			</ScrollReveal>
			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.1}>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12">
					My background, my approach and why I started Silverbeet Technology
				</p>
			</ScrollReveal>

			<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h2>Overview</h2>
					<p>
						For over 25 years, I’ve made technology work for people — from
						helping users troubleshoot their desktop systems, to building
						infrastructure for development teams to collaborate and write code
						on, to securing networks, all while architecting reliable systems
						that scale. I founded Silverbeet Technology to bring principled,
						practical tech solutions to individuals and small businesses who
						want their technology to just work, without unnecessary complexity.
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>

				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h3>My background spans</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>
							My early IT years started with me supporting user's desktops
							systems, followed by learning end-to-end networking configuration,
							running cables from systems back to the servers, before finally
							moving on to understanding and running various servers; from Novel
							NetWare, Windows NT, Solaris, and Linux
						</li>
						<li>
							Thanks to my early Linux exposure I have deep experience with, and
							a strong interest in Linux, as well as open source software in
							general. Reading books like Eric S. Raymond's "The Cathedral and
							the Bazar" and Linus Torvalds "Just for Fun: The Story of an
							Accidental Revolutionary" helped me understand open source and the
							sea change its ideas provided. It was a wake up call for me, and
							I've excitedly followed that path ever since
						</li>
						<li>
							I have a strong foundation in DevOps, from automating system
							infrastructure configuration, building pipelines for CI/CD,
							architecting reproducible infrastructure, all setup using
							infrastructure as code ideals. I've always shared my ideas in
							order to help others utilize tools and follow best practices. I'm
							a strong believer that much of my work is thanks to me standing on
							the shoulders of giants, so I feel the need to constantly pay that
							forward
						</li>
						<li>
							I've given talks and shared technical presentations to teams,
							groups and students around the world, while my security research
							led me to give talks at premier information security conferences
							like DEF CON and BSidesLV. My work in the biodiversity realm
							allowed me to work with non-profits, universities and museums, and
							allowed me to publish position papers outlining sustainable server
							architecture to house, and share, biodiversity data
						</li>
					</ul>
					<p>
						I believe in making tech understandable, dependable, and secure —
						whether that means optimizing a server stack, hardening a web
						service, or automating a build pipeline, all while being open and
						transparent with my approaches and documenting the solutions I've
						built
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>

				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h3>What drives me</h3>
					<p>
						From the moment I discovered open source in 1999, I’ve been
						passionate about software freedom, community developed tools, and
						solutions that empower users. That curiosity turned into a career in
						helping people solve real tech challenges with fresh ideas
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>

				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h3>My approach</h3>
					<p>
						Rather than pushing expensive, proprietary software or complex tools
						for their own sake, I focus on:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<ol>
							✔ Using open source and proven DevOps practices where applicable
						</ol>
						<ol>
							✔ Automating configuration, builds and deployments for reliability
							and reproducibility
						</ol>
						<ol>
							✔ Making systems secure by design from the start — not something
							bolted on later
						</ol>
						<ol>
							✔ Sharing my knowledge to help clients decide when to buy vs when
							use open source tools that are often as mature as proprietary
							alternatives
						</ol>
					</ul>
					<p>
						If you’re looking for straight-forward but powerful IT and security
						solutions with the future in mind — I’m here to talk about what will
						work best to achieve your goals. Feel free to
						<a
							href="/contact/"
							class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
							>contact</a
						> me to start a dialog.
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>
